&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Facilities Department – Catering&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Robertson Centre, Kidderminster&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Facilities Support Worker – Catering&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£9.21 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post 1:         14 Hours per week - Mon / Wed /Thurs / Fri  15.30-19.00&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post 2:         12 Hours per week - Thurs / Fri / Sat / Sun  11.00-14.00&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to work within a busy and varied environment, working alongside our clinical and other non-clinical colleagues to make a positive contribution to our patients and staff experience. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS pension  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dedicated training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Progression and apprenticeship opportunities  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Generous annual leave allowance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of catering in an employed capacity is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Sue Jeynes on 07876592703.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;All staff whatever their role, level or responsibility will be encouraged and supported to do their job well and to improve their job.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Making Every Day Better for patients, staff, service users and carers is the responsibility of all of us and we want to embed a culture within the organisation that encourages and supports the drive to improve what we do.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications for this role will be considered in adherence with the Working Time Regulations policy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
